# DEV TOOLING ONLY. Do not use this file to configure the installed plugin.
#
# This .env is read only by `npm run smoke` (the live-API smoke test in
# mcp/scripts/smoke.ts). The Spiffy MCP server has NO dotenv loader, so
# nothing set here ever reaches the running plugin.
#
# Do NOT copy or save this file as ~/.config/spiffy-plugin/config.toml.
# That path requires TOML syntax (api_key = "...") and now loudly rejects
# dotenv-style SPIFFY_API_KEY=... content with a specific error.
#
# End users - configure the plugin via the README "Configure your API key"
# section (the SPIFFY_API_KEY environment variable, or a TOML
# ~/.config/spiffy-plugin/config.toml). Not this file.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# For local `npm run smoke` only, set ONE of the following.
#
# 1. Paste your key directly.
# SPIFFY_API_KEY=your_64_character_hex_key_here
#
# 2. Reference 1Password (requires the `op` CLI installed and signed in).
# SPIFFY_API_KEY=op://YourVault/Spiffy API/credential
#
# Get your key from the Spiffy dashboard under Settings - API. Current
# Spiffy keys are 64-character hex strings without a prefix (no sk_live_).
#
# Optional smoke overrides.
# SPIFFY_BASE_URL=https://api.spiffy.co
# SPIFFY_DRY_RUN=0   # 1 blocks all writes (synthetic responses), useful for testing
